data.description: Owning a 110 year old home isn't about acquiring a property, it's about becoming a custodian of history.  Step into an era of formal rooms and elegance.  This home is situated in a charming historic district,  Enjoy modern comforts and the architecture of days gone by.  The beautiful hardwood floors are inviting, the downstairs master offers a beamed ceiling, a cozy fireplace, and full bathroom.  The formal dining room with a built-in cabinet is situated just outside of the kitchen; which boasts modern stainless steel appliances and a walk in pantry.  Upstairs you'll find a collection of bedrooms each with it's own unique character.  The larger bedroom features cove ceilings, double closets, and a fireplace.  The full bathroom is situated just outside of this room.  There is a half bath with an adjoining bedroom as well.  Beyond the historic splendor, this home is ideally located and close to schools and shopping. Detached workshop. Shared driveway.
